grbl g-code parser
    read lines
        ignore chars
            c <= ' '
            c == '/'
        ignore range
            c == '('
                until next ')'
            c == ';'
                until end of line / eof
        char count >= 79 == overflow
    line
        ignore empty line
        line[0] == '$'
            system_execute_line
                TODO
        else
            zero or more:
                {A-Z}{float}
https://linuxcnc.org/docs/html/gcode/overview.html#cha:g-code-overview
    each line is called a block
    each block may contain commands
    file containing lines/blocks is called a program
    a line of code
        one or more words
        a word is a letter followed by a number
        a word may either be a command or argument to a command
